'''Karin Maria Bruzelius''' (born 19 February 1941) is a Swedish-Norwegian judge.

She was born in [[Lund]], [[Sweden]],<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia |year=|title=Karin Maria Bruzelius|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Karin_Maria_Bruzelius|language=Norwegian|accessdate=17 February 2011}}</ref> graduated as [[cand.jur.]] from [[Lund University]] in 1964 and Master of Law from [[Columbia Law School]] in 1969. She worked in the [[Norwegian Ministry of Justice and the Police]] from 1965, and became deputy under-secretary of State there in 1979. From 1983 to 1987 she worked as a lawyer, before returning as deputy under-secretary of State. She was promoted to permanent under-secretary of State in 1989, as the first female to hold such a position. She is a [[Supreme Court of Norway|Supreme Court Justice]] from 1997 to 2011.<ref name=hvem>{{cite book|title=Bruzelius, Karin M. |book=Hvem er hvem?|chapter=Bruzelius, Karin|year=2008 |editor=[[Knut Olav <U+00C5>m<U+00E5>s|<U+00C5>m<U+00E5>s, Knut Olav]] |publisher=Aschehoug |location=Oslo |isbn=978-82-03-23561-0 |pages=81|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

She has chaired the [[Petroleumsr<U+00E5>det|Petroleum Council]] (1987<U+2013>2004) as well as [[The Norwegian Association for Women's Rights]].<ref name=hvem/>

On 5 February 2008, the Standing Committee on Scrutiny and Constitutional Affairs of the [[Stortinget|Norwegian Parliament]] recommended that a commission be named to investigate and, if warranted, prosecute for [[Impeachment (Norway)|impeachment]] three of the Norwegian Supreme Court Justices who presided over the cases of [[Fritz Moen]], a victim of [[miscarriage of justice]]. The three were Bruzelius, [[Magnus Matningsdal]] and [[Eilert Stang Lund]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Robert |last=Gjerde |title= Stortinget m<U+00E5> vurdere riksrett |url=http://www.aftenposten.no/nyheter/iriks/article2238528.ece |work=[[Aftenposten]] |date=5 February 2008 |accessdate=5 February 2008 |language= Norwegian }}</ref> However, when the case was treated by the Standing Committee on Justice three months later, it was closed.<ref>{{cite news |first=Else Gro |last=Ommundsen |title=H<U+00F8>yesterettsdommere stilles ikke for riksrett |url=http://www.dagsavisen.no/innenriks/article348162.ece |work=[[Dagsavisen]] |date=8 May 2008 |accessdate=12 October 2008 |language= Norwegian }}</ref>

